body:
Thanks for taking the time to report this.

Can you please attach an example that shows the issue or missing feature?  (Must be openly licensed, completely self-contained so can directly run what you provide. Ideally use test_regress format, see https://veripool.org/guide/latest/contributing.html?highlight=test_regress#reporting-bugs)

```
package pk1;
   typedef struct packed {
      int AddrBits;
      int DataBits;
   } cfg_t;
endpackage

virtual class a_class_t #(parameter pk1::cfg_t CFG=0);
   localparam type addr_t = logic [CFG.AddrBits-1:0];
   localparam type data_t = logic [CFG.DataBits-1:0];

   typedef struct packed {
      addr_t addr;
      data_t data;
   } pkt_t;
endclass

interface a_if #(parameter pk1::cfg_t Cfg=0);
   a_class_t#(Cfg)::pkt_t p;
   //modport initiator (
   //   output p
   //);
endinterface

module a_to_b #(
   parameter pk1::cfg_t ACFG = 0
)(
   //a_if.initiator bus
   a_if bus
);
  // sturf
endmodule

module the_top();
   localparam pk1::cfg_t acfg = '{
      AddrBits : 64
      ,DataBits :  64
   };

   a_if #(.Cfg(acfg)) the_bus();

   a_to_b #(acfg) a_to_b(
      .bus(the_bus)
   );
endmodule
```

What output from that test indicates it is wrong, and what is the correct or expected output?  (Or, please make test self-checking if possible.)

```
@easyemachine verilator_fixes % verilator -cc -Wno-ASCRANGE test1.sv
%Error: Internal Error: test1.sv:10:29: ../V3Param.cpp:452: Couldn't find pin in clone list
                                      : ... note: In instance 'the_top.a_to_b'
   10 |    localparam type data_t = logic [CFG.DataBits-1:0];
      |                             ^~~~~
                        ... See the manual at https://verilator.org/verilator_doc.html?v=5.041 for more assistance.

```

What 'verilator' command line do we use to run your example?

```
verilator -cc -Wno-ASCRANGE test1.sv
```

What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?  Did you try it with other simulators?

This used to build with:
```
@easyemachine verilator_fixes % /opt/verilator.20250724/bin/verilator --version
Verilator 5.039 devel rev v5.038-88-g895b85a16

@easyemachine verilator_fixes % /opt/verilator.20250724/bin/verilator --cc --Wno-ASCRANGE test1.sv
- V e r i l a t i o n   R e p o r t: Verilator 5.039 devel rev v5.038-88-g895b85a16
- Verilator: Built from 0.025 MB sources in 7 modules, into 0.024 MB in 12 C++ files needing 0.000 MB
- Verilator: Walltime 0.024 s (elab=0.005, cvt=0.009, bld=0.000); cpu 0.008 s on 1 threads

```
